{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":10182,"record_hash":"sha256:2a728e16dc4da2e061529d9c22a40a7fd3075edbac7fc39e20f32bf5fb621be1","timestamp":"2026-05-07T20:57:34.080Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Store the session key under a key-shaped name\\\" body=\\\"This writes `plan.session_key` under the `session-id` GitMeta key whenever a raw session ID exists. The value is intentionally a hash/key, so the storage name now lies about both semantics and privacy; a maintainer or consumer could reasonably treat it as the original session id. Use a `session-key` or `session-id-hash` key, or store a redacted session id separately if that is actually needed.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=219 end=220 priority=2 confidence=0.82}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Avoid cloning large transcript records for redaction\\\" body=\\\"`redact_value` clones the entire `serde_json::Value`, and the production caller reaches it from a borrowed `TranscriptRecord` in `TranscriptEnvelope::new`. Agent records can carry large prompt/tool payloads, so every appended record briefly keeps both the unredacted and redacted tree. Since `GitMetaCaptureInput.records` is already owned by the write path, moving `source_record` into redaction would remove this clone without changing behavior.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs\\\" start=16 end=18 priority=2 confidence=0.78}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Preserve malformed transcript entry context\\\" body=\\\"When rebuilding transcript hashes from the stored list, any malformed envelope is collapsed to `existing GitMeta transcript entry for key ... is malformed`. That drops the serde error and the list position, so the fallback path that should recover from missing hash-set state becomes hard to repair when one entry is corrupt. Use `enumerate()` and `with_context` around `serde_json::from_str` so callers get the key plus offending entry index while preserving the parse error.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=191 end=195 priority=3 confidence=0.86}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Keep JSON capture output structured\\\" body=\\\"`CaptureReport` has `target`, `records_new`, and `transcript_records_appended`, but `run_from_current_dir` flattens those fields into one human sentence before returning the public `CommandOutput`. The `but` JSON path serializes this same type, leaving machine callers to parse prose and making future wording changes observable. Keeping named fields on `CommandOutput` and deriving `Display` from them preserves the current human output while tightening the public surface.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs\\\" start=63 end=68 priority=3 confidence=0.75}\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T20:57:34.080Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}